<TITLE> BM College students block road </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, June 16 (bdnews24.com)Students of BM College in Barisal took to streets after a co-student was stabbed on Tuesday. The demonstrators blocked the road in front of the college and brought out a protest rally outside the campus. The police brought the situation under control after the students were assured of measures against the perpetrator. According to witnesses, a youth named 'Jashim' was teasing the college girls in front of the college at around 10:30am. A third-year economics student, Tanvir Hossain, asked Jashim to get out of the campus and an argument started off. At one point, Jashim stabbed Tanvir and fled the scene. Tanvir was immediately rushed to Barisal Sadar Hospital and later to Sher-e-Bangla Medical College Hospital as his condition deteriorated. Barisal Metropolitan Police assistant commissioner Hayatul Islam Khan said they were trying to arrest Jashim. bdn
